<DOC><DOCNO> AP880902-0045 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-02-88 0213EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Himalayas-Quake     09-02 0136</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Himalayas-Quake,0141</SECOND><HEAD>Temblor Rocks Nepal</HEAD><DATELINE>KATMANDU, Nepal (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A mild earthquake hit Nepal today, 12days after a strong quake that killed hundreds of people, but therewere no reports of damage or casualties, scientists said.   The quake registered 4.8 on the Richter scale, according toseismologists. They said it was recorded at 3:45 a.m.   They described the tremor as an aftershock of the 6.5 quake Aug.21 that killed more than 1,000 people in Nepal and India.   Like that quake, the epicenter of today's quake was in Udayapur,20 miles north of the India-Nepal border.   The Richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded onseismographs.   An earthquake of 3.5 on the Richter scale can cause slightdamage in the local area, 4 moderate damage, 5 considerable damage,6 severe damage.</TEXT></DOC>